    Function reference

    Primary functions

    These functions are exported and therefore available after calling library(), or using ‘::’ notation

    Aggregate

    aggregate_data()
    Aggregate line list datasets
    resume_cycle_aggregation()
    Resume data aggregation
    recombine_input_data()
    Recombine input datasets

    Validate

    validate_input_data()
    Validate input datasets before aggregating

    Generate

    generate_synthetic_data()
    Generate synthetic input datasets

    Internal functions

    These functions are not exported, but are used by primary functions (accessible with ‘:::’ notation). It is not necessary to manually call any of these functions.

    Aggregate

    aggregate_data_concurrent()
    Aggregate data with concurrent comparators
    aggregate_data_descriptive_outcomes()
    Aggregate AESI outcomes
    aggregate_data_descriptive_vaccinations()
    Aggregate vaccinations
    aggregate_data_exposed()
    Aggregate post-vaccination exposure data
    aggregate_data_historic()
    Aggregate historic data
    aggregate_data_self()
    Aggregate data with self controls
    concurrent_final_aggregation()
    Complete aggregation of data with concurrent comparators
